  title: Frontal Lobe
  description: The frontal lobe is located at the front part of the brain and plays
    a crucial role in higher cognitive functions. It controls reasoning, emotional
    regulation, personality expression, and motor control. The primary motor cortex,
    located in the frontal lobe, controls voluntary muscle movements.
